{"title_page": "Kriszti\u00e1n Grecs\u00f3", "text_new": "{{eastern name order|Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n}}\n{{Infobox writer <!-- for more information see [[:Template:Infobox writer/doc]] -->\n| name = Kriszti\u00e1n Grecs\u00f3\n| image = Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n (cropped).jpg\n| image_size = \n| caption = Kriszti\u00e1n Grecs\u00f3\n| birth_name = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1976|5|18|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Szegv\u00e1r]], [[Hungary]]\n| occupation = Writer, poet\n| nationality = [[Hungarians|Hungarian]]\n| genre = \n| subject = \n| movement = \n| notableworks = {{plainlist|\n* ''Pletykaanyu'' (2001)\n* ''Megyek ut\u00e1nad'' (2011)\n* ''Mellettem elf\u00e9rsz'' (2014)\n* ''Vera'' (2019)\n}}\n| influences = \n| influenced = \n| awards = [[Attila J\u00f3zsef Prize]] (2006)\n| website = {{URL|http://grecso.hu/}}\n}}\n'''Kriszti\u00e1n Grecs\u00f3''' (born 18 May 1976) is a Hungarian writer, poet and editor.\n\n==Biography==\nGrecs\u00f3 was born in [[Szegv\u00e1r]] on 18 May 1976. His younger brother, {{ill|Zolt\u00e1n Grecs\u00f3|hu|Grecs\u00f3 Zolt\u00e1n}}, is a dancer and choreographer.<ref name=\"delmagyarblaho\">{{cite news |last1=Blah\u00f3 |first1=Gabriella |title=Grecs\u00f3-l\u00e1zban \u00e9gett Szegv\u00e1r |url=https://library.hungaricana.hu/hu/view/Delmagyarorszag_2007_08/?pg=354&layout=s |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=[[D\u00e9lmagyarorsz\u00e1g]] |volume=97 |issue=195 |page=7 |date=22 August 2007 |language=Hungarian}}</ref> He graduated from the {{ill|J\u00e1nos Bats\u00e1nyi High School|hu|Csongr\u00e1di Bats\u00e1nyi J\u00e1nos Gimn\u00e1zium, Szakk\u00f6z\u00e9piskola \u00e9s Koll\u00e9gium}} in [[Csongr\u00e1d]]. In 2001, he received a diploma in Hungarian language and literature from the [[University of Szeged|Attila J\u00f3zsef University]] in [[Szeged]].<ref name=\"delmagyarblaho\" /><ref name=\"magvetobio\">{{cite web |title=Szerz\u0151k: Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n |url=https://magveto.hu/index.php?action=szerzo&id=49 |publisher=Magvet\u0151 Kiad\u00f3 |accessdate=19 April 2020 |language=Hungarian}}</ref>\n\nBetween 2001 and 2006, Grecs\u00f3 worked as an editor for the ''{{ill|B\u00e1rka|hu|B\u00e1rka (foly\u00f3irat)}}'' literary journal in [[B\u00e9k\u00e9scsaba]]. From 2007 to 2009, he was the lead editor<!--vezet\u0151szerkezt\u0151--> of the ''{{ill|N\u0151k Lapja|hu}}'' women's magazine. In 2009, he became the lead editor of the prose and essay section of ''[[\u00c9let \u00e9s Irodalom]]''.<ref name=\"magvetobio\" /><ref name=\"aegonbio\">{{cite web |title=A 2012-es AEGON M\u0171v\u00e9szeti D\u00edj kit\u00fcntetettje: Grecs\u00f3 Kriszt\u00e1n Mellettem elf\u00e9rsz c\u00edm\u0171 reg\u00e9ny\u00e9\u00e9rt |url=https://www.aegon.hu/hirek/2012-es-aegon-muveszeti-dij-kituntetettje.html |publisher=AEGON Biztos\u00edt\u00f3 |accessdate=19 April 2020 |language=Hungarian}}</ref>\n\nIn 2001, he achieved widespread fame with his short story collection ''Pletykaanyu'' (\"Gossip Mom\").<ref name=\"forraspletyka\">{{cite journal |last1=Szab\u00f3 |first1=Tibor |title=Tiszt\u00edtott pr\u00f3zasz\u00f6vet \u2014 puszt\u00edt\u00f3 referencialit\u00e1s: ''Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n: Pletykaanyu'' |journal=[[Forr\u00e1s]] |date=May 2007 |volume=39 |issue=5 |page=105 |url=http://www.forrasfolyoirat.hu/0705/szabo.pdf |accessdate=19 April 2020 |language=Hungarian |issn=0133-056X }}</ref> This was followed by a number of successful novels: ''Isten hozott'' (\"Welcome\", 2005),<ref>{{cite news |last1=Benedek |first1=Anna |title=M\u00e1s-vil\u00e1g: Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n: Isten hozott, Magvet\u0151, 2005 |url=https://litera.hu/magazin/kritika/mas-vilag.html |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=Litera |date=20 June 2005 |language=Hungarian}}</ref>  ''T\u00e1nciskola'' (\"Dance School\", 2008),<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Darvasi |first1=Ferenc |title=Kritika: Isten hozott, T\u00e1nciskola! |journal=[[Tiszat\u00e1j]] |date=July 2008 |volume=62 |issue=7 |page=92 |url=http://epa.oszk.hu/00700/00713/00203/pdf/tiszataj_EPA00713_2008_07_084-092.pdf |accessdate=19 April 2020 |language=Hungarian |issn=0133-1167}}</ref> ''Mellettem elf\u00e9rsz'' (\"You Fit Beside Me\", 2011),<ref>{{cite news |last1=Bazs\u00e1nyi |first1=S\u00e1ndor |title=Nem csak elk\u00e9pzeli: Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n: Mellettem elf\u00e9rsz, Magvet\u0151, 2011 |url=https://litera.hu/magazin/kritika/nem-csak-elkepzeli.html |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=Litera |date=26 March 2011 |language=Hungarian}}</ref> ''Megyek ut\u00e1nad'' (\"I Follow You\", 2014),<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Horv\u00e1th |first1=Csaba |title=Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n: Megyek ut\u00e1nad |journal=[[Kort\u00e1rs]] |date=November 2011 |volume=58 |issue=11 |url=https://www.kortarsfolyoirat.hu/archivum/2014/11/arch-grecso-krisztian-megyek-utanad.html |accessdate=19 April 2020 |language=Hungarian |issn=0023-415X}}</ref> ''Jelmezb\u00e1l'' (\"Costume Ball\", 2016)<ref>{{cite journal |last1=T\u0151t\u0151s |first1=Dorottya |title=Hol volt, hol nem volt, volt egyszer a reg\u00e9ny |journal=[[Helikon (journal)|Helikon]] |date=25 June 2017 |volume=28 |issue=14 |url=https://www.helikon.ro/hol-volt-hol-nem-volt-volt-egyszer-a-regeny/ |accessdate=19 April 2020 |language=Hungarian |issn=1220-6288}}</ref> and ''Vera'' (2019).<ref>{{cite news |author1=horner |title=Szomor\u00fa-izgul\u00e1s \u2013 Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n Vera c\u00edm\u0171 reg\u00e9ny\u00e9r\u0151l |url=https://nepszava.hu/3029710_szomoru-izgulas-grecso-krisztian-vera-cimu-regenyerol |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=[[N\u00e9pszava]] |date=24 March 2019 |language=Hungarian}}</ref>\n\nGrecs\u00f3 also worked as a screenwriter for the films ''{{ill|Hasutasok|hu}}'' (2007) and ''{{ill|Megy a g\u0151z\u00f6s|hu}}'' (2007).<ref name=\"delmagyarblaho\" /> He wrote the book of the highly successful musical ''{{ill|A P\u00e1l utcai fi\u00fak (musical)|hu|lt=A P\u00e1l utcai fi\u00fak}}'', based on [[Ferenc Moln\u00e1r]]'s novel ''[[The Paul Street Boys]]'', which premiered in the [[Comedy Theatre of Budapest]] on 5 November 2016.<ref name=\"ligetpuf\">{{cite news |title=A P\u00e1l utcai fi\u00fak: legyen szabad a Grund! |url=https://liget.ro/studio/a-pal-utcai-fiuk-legyen-szabad-a-grund |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=Liget.ro |date=25 October 2019 |language=Hungarian}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Matalin |first1=D\u00f3ra |title=Mi\u00e9rt nem lehet jegyet kapni a P\u00e1l utcai fi\u00fakra? |url=https://index.hu/kultur/2019/05/31/a_pal_utcai_fiuk_vigszinhaz_eloadas_musical_jegyek/ |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=[[Index (Hungarian website)|Index]] |date=31 May 2019 |language=Hungarian}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nHe is married to Judit \u00c1rvai, a press relations associate of the {{ill|Magvet\u0151 K\u00f6nyvkiad\u00f3|hu|lt=Magvet\u0151}} publishing house.<ref>{{cite news |last1=M\u00e9sz\u00e1ros |first1=M\u00e1rton |title=Egy vil\u00e1g, ahonnan n\u00e9zni lehet az \u00e9letet |url=https://kulturpart.hu/2017/10/05/egy_vilag_ahonnan_nezni_lehet_az_eletet |accessdate=20 April 2020 |work=Kult\u00farpart |date=5 October 2017 |language=Hungarian}}</ref> In 2019, they adopted a girl, Hanna.<ref>{{cite news |last1=J\u00e1nossy |first1=Vill\u0151 |title=Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n betegs\u00e9ge miatt egy id\u0151re leker\u00fclt az \u00f6r\u00f6kbefogad\u00e1si v\u00e1r\u00f3list\u00e1r\u00f3l |url=https://24.hu/kultura/2019/10/22/grecso-krisztian-huzos-atv-spirit-orokbefogadas/ |accessdate=20 April 2020 |work=[[24.hu]] |date=22 October 2019 |language=Hungarian}}</ref> In October 2018, Grecs\u00f3 was diagnosed with [[Human papillomavirus infection|HPV]]-associated [[head and neck cancer]]. He recovered in early 2019.<ref>{{cite news |title=R\u00e1kbetegs\u00e9g\u00e9r\u0151l vallott Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n |url=https://hvg.hu/kultura/20190215_Rakbetegsegerol_vallott_Grecso_Krisztian |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=[[Heti Vil\u00e1ggazdas\u00e1g|HVG]] |date=15 February 2019 |language=Hungarian}}</ref>\n\n==Works==\n* ''Angyalkacsin\u00e1l\u00e1s'' (1999; poetry)\n* ''Pletykaanyu'' (2001; short stories)\n* ''Isten hozott'' (2005; novel)\n* ''T\u00e1nciskola'' (2008; novel)\n* ''Mellettem elf\u00e9rsz'' (2011; novel)\n* ''Megyek ut\u00e1nad'' (2014; novel)\n* ''Jelmezb\u00e1l: Egy csal\u00e1dreg\u00e9ny mozaikjai'' (2016; novel)\n* ''Harminc \u00e9v naps\u00fct\u00e9s'' (2017; short stories)\n* ''Vera'' (2019; novel)\n* ''Magamr\u00f3l t\u00f6bbet'' (2020; poetry)\n\n==Awards and honours==\n* [[S\u00e1ndor Br\u00f3dy Prize]] (2002)<ref name=\"magvetobio\" />\n* {{ill|Gy\u00f6rgy Faludy Prize|hu|Faludy Gy\u00f6rgy-d\u00edj}} (2004)<ref name=\"magvetobio\" />\n* {{ill|Tibor D\u00e9ry Prize|hu|D\u00e9ry Tibor-d\u00edj}} (2004)<ref name=\"magvetobio\" />\n* [[Attila J\u00f3zsef Prize]] (2006)<ref name=\"magvetobio\" />\n* {{ill|AEGON Art Prize|hu|AEGON m\u0171v\u00e9szeti d\u00edj}} (2012)<ref name=\"magvetobio\" /><ref name=\"aegonbio\" />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Grecso, Krisztian}}\n[[Category:Hungarian male novelists]]\n[[Category:Hungarian male poets]]\n[[Category:21st-century Hungarian novelists]]\n[[Category:21st-century Hungarian male writers]]\n[[Category:Attila J\u00f3zsef Prize recipients]]\n[[Category:1976 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{eastern name order|Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n}}\n{{Infobox writer <!-- for more information see [[:Template:Infobox writer/doc]] -->\n| name = Kriszti\u00e1n Grecs\u00f3\n| image = Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n (cropped).jpg\n| image_size = \n| caption = Kriszti\u00e1n Grecs\u00f3\n| birth_name = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1976|5|18|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Szegv\u00e1r]], [[Hungary]]\n| occupation = Writer, poet\n| nationality = [[Hungarians|Hungarian]]\n| genre = \n| subject = \n| movement = \n| notableworks = {{plainlist|\n* ''Pletykaanyu'' (2001)\n* ''Megyek ut\u00e1nad'' (2011)\n* ''Mellettem elf\u00e9rsz'' (2014)\n* ''Vera'' (2019)\n}}\n| influences = \n| influenced = \n| awards = [[Attila J\u00f3zsef Prize]] (2006)\n| website = {{URL|http://grecso.hu/}}\n}}\n'''Kriszti\u00e1n Grecs\u00f3''' (born 18 May 1976) is a Hungarian writer, poet and editor.\n\n==Biography==\nGrecs\u00f3 was born in [[Szegv\u00e1r]] on 18 May 1976. His younger brother, {{ill|Zolt\u00e1n Grecs\u00f3|hu|Grecs\u00f3 Zolt\u00e1n}}, is a dancer and choreographer.<ref name=\"delmagyarblaho\">{{cite news |last1=Blah\u00f3 |first1=Gabriella |title=Grecs\u00f3-l\u00e1zban \u00e9gett Szegv\u00e1r |url=https://library.hungaricana.hu/hu/view/Delmagyarorszag_2007_08/?pg=354&layout=s |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=[[D\u00e9lmagyarorsz\u00e1g]] |volume=97 |issue=195 |page=7 |date=22 August 2007 |language=Hungarian}}</ref> He graduated from the {{ill|J\u00e1nos Bats\u00e1nyi High School|hu|Csongr\u00e1di Bats\u00e1nyi J\u00e1nos Gimn\u00e1zium, Szakk\u00f6z\u00e9piskola \u00e9s Koll\u00e9gium}} in [[Csongr\u00e1d]]. In 2001, he received a diploma in Hungarian language and literature from the [[University of Szeged|Attila J\u00f3zsef University]] in [[Szeged]].<ref name=\"delmagyarblaho\" /><ref name=\"magvetobio\">{{cite web |title=Szerz\u0151k: Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n |url=https://magveto.hu/index.php?action=szerzo&id=49 |publisher=Magvet\u0151 Kiad\u00f3 |accessdate=19 April 2020 |language=Hungarian}}</ref>\n\nBetween 2001 and 2006, Grecs\u00f3 worked as an editor for the ''{{ill|B\u00e1rka|hu|B\u00e1rka (foly\u00f3irat)}}'' literary journal in [[B\u00e9k\u00e9scsaba]]. From 2007 to 2009, he was the lead editor<!--vezet\u0151szerkezt\u0151--> of the ''{{ill|N\u0151k Lapja|hu}}'' women's magazine. In 2009, he became the lead editor of the prose and essay section of ''[[\u00c9let \u00e9s Irodalom]]''.<ref name=\"magvetobio\" /><ref name=\"aegonbio\">{{cite web |title=A 2012-es AEGON M\u0171v\u00e9szeti D\u00edj kit\u00fcntetettje: Grecs\u00f3 Kriszt\u00e1n Mellettem elf\u00e9rsz c\u00edm\u0171 reg\u00e9ny\u00e9\u00e9rt |url=https://www.aegon.hu/hirek/2012-es-aegon-muveszeti-dij-kituntetettje.html |publisher=AEGON Biztos\u00edt\u00f3 |accessdate=19 April 2020 |language=Hungarian}}</ref>\n\nIn 2001, he achieved widespread fame with his short story collection ''Pletykaanyu'' (\"Gossip Mom\").<ref name=\"forraspletyka\">{{cite journal |last1=Szab\u00f3 |first1=Tibor |title=Tiszt\u00edtott pr\u00f3zasz\u00f6vet \u2014 puszt\u00edt\u00f3 referencialit\u00e1s: ''Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n: Pletykaanyu'' |journal=[[Forr\u00e1s]] |date=May 2007 |volume=39 |issue=5 |page=105 |url=http://www.forrasfolyoirat.hu/0705/szabo.pdf |accessdate=19 April 2020 |language=Hungarian |issn=0133-056X }}</ref> This was followed by a number of successful novels: ''Isten hozott'' (\"Welcome\", 2005),<ref>{{cite news |last1=Benedek |first1=Anna |title=M\u00e1s-vil\u00e1g: Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n: Isten hozott, Magvet\u0151, 2005 |url=https://litera.hu/magazin/kritika/mas-vilag.html |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=Litera |date=20 June 2005 |language=Hungarian}}</ref>  ''T\u00e1nciskola'' (\"Dance School\", 2008),<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Darvasi |first1=Ferenc |title=Kritika: Isten hozott, T\u00e1nciskola! |journal=[[Tiszat\u00e1j]] |date=July 2008 |volume=62 |issue=7 |page=92 |url=http://epa.oszk.hu/00700/00713/00203/pdf/tiszataj_EPA00713_2008_07_084-092.pdf |accessdate=19 April 2020 |language=Hungarian |issn=0133-1167}}</ref> ''Mellettem elf\u00e9rsz'' (\"You Fit Beside Me\", 2011),<ref>{{cite news |last1=Bazs\u00e1nyi |first1=S\u00e1ndor |title=Nem csak elk\u00e9pzeli: Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n: Mellettem elf\u00e9rsz, Magvet\u0151, 2011 |url=https://litera.hu/magazin/kritika/nem-csak-elkepzeli.html |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=Litera |date=26 March 2011 |language=Hungarian}}</ref> ''Megyek ut\u00e1nad'' (\"I Follow You\", 2014),<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Horv\u00e1th |first1=Csaba |title=Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n: Megyek ut\u00e1nad |journal=[[Kort\u00e1rs]] |date=November 2011 |volume=58 |issue=11 |url=https://www.kortarsfolyoirat.hu/archivum/2014/11/arch-grecso-krisztian-megyek-utanad.html |accessdate=19 April 2020 |language=Hungarian |issn=0023-415X}}</ref> ''Jelmezb\u00e1l'' (\"Costume Ball\", 2016)<ref>{{cite journal |last1=T\u0151t\u0151s |first1=Dorottya |title=Hol volt, hol nem volt, volt egyszer a reg\u00e9ny |journal=[[Helikon (journal)|Helikon]] |date=25 June 2017 |volume=28 |issue=14 |url=https://www.helikon.ro/hol-volt-hol-nem-volt-volt-egyszer-a-regeny/ |accessdate=19 April 2020 |language=Hungarian |issn=1220-6288}}</ref> and ''Vera'' (2019).<ref>{{cite news |author1=horner |title=Szomor\u00fa-izgul\u00e1s \u2013 Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n Vera c\u00edm\u0171 reg\u00e9ny\u00e9r\u0151l |url=https://nepszava.hu/3029710_szomoru-izgulas-grecso-krisztian-vera-cimu-regenyerol |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=[[N\u00e9pszava]] |date=24 March 2019 |language=Hungarian}}</ref>\n\nGrecs\u00f3 also worked as a screenwriter for the films ''{{ill|Hasutasok|hu}}'' (2006) and ''{{ill|Megy a g\u0151z\u00f6s|hu}}'' (2007).<ref name=\"delmagyarblaho\" /> He wrote the book of the highly successful musical ''{{ill|A P\u00e1l utcai fi\u00fak (musical)|hu|lt=A P\u00e1l utcai fi\u00fak}}'', based on [[Ferenc Moln\u00e1r]]'s novel ''[[The Paul Street Boys]]'', which premiered in the [[Comedy Theatre of Budapest]] on 5 November 2016.<ref name=\"ligetpuf\">{{cite news |title=A P\u00e1l utcai fi\u00fak: legyen szabad a Grund! |url=https://liget.ro/studio/a-pal-utcai-fiuk-legyen-szabad-a-grund |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=Liget.ro |date=25 October 2019 |language=Hungarian}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Matalin |first1=D\u00f3ra |title=Mi\u00e9rt nem lehet jegyet kapni a P\u00e1l utcai fi\u00fakra? |url=https://index.hu/kultur/2019/05/31/a_pal_utcai_fiuk_vigszinhaz_eloadas_musical_jegyek/ |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=[[Index (Hungarian website)|Index]] |date=31 May 2019 |language=Hungarian}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nHe is married to Judit \u00c1rvai, a press relations associate of the {{ill|Magvet\u0151 K\u00f6nyvkiad\u00f3|hu|lt=Magvet\u0151}} publishing house.<ref>{{cite news |last1=M\u00e9sz\u00e1ros |first1=M\u00e1rton |title=Egy vil\u00e1g, ahonnan n\u00e9zni lehet az \u00e9letet |url=https://kulturpart.hu/2017/10/05/egy_vilag_ahonnan_nezni_lehet_az_eletet |accessdate=20 April 2020 |work=Kult\u00farpart |date=5 October 2017 |language=Hungarian}}</ref> In 2019, they adopted a girl, Hanna.<ref>{{cite news |last1=J\u00e1nossy |first1=Vill\u0151 |title=Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n betegs\u00e9ge miatt egy id\u0151re leker\u00fclt az \u00f6r\u00f6kbefogad\u00e1si v\u00e1r\u00f3list\u00e1r\u00f3l |url=https://24.hu/kultura/2019/10/22/grecso-krisztian-huzos-atv-spirit-orokbefogadas/ |accessdate=20 April 2020 |work=[[24.hu]] |date=22 October 2019 |language=Hungarian}}</ref> In October 2018, Grecs\u00f3 was diagnosed with [[Human papillomavirus infection|HPV]]-associated [[head and neck cancer]]. He recovered in early 2019.<ref>{{cite news |title=R\u00e1kbetegs\u00e9g\u00e9r\u0151l vallott Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n |url=https://hvg.hu/kultura/20190215_Rakbetegsegerol_vallott_Grecso_Krisztian |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=[[Heti Vil\u00e1ggazdas\u00e1g|HVG]] |date=15 February 2019 |language=Hungarian}}</ref>\n\n==Works==\n* ''Angyalkacsin\u00e1l\u00e1s'' (1999; poetry)\n* ''Pletykaanyu'' (2001; short stories)\n* ''Isten hozott'' (2005; novel)\n* ''T\u00e1nciskola'' (2008; novel)\n* ''Mellettem elf\u00e9rsz'' (2011; novel)\n* ''Megyek ut\u00e1nad'' (2014; novel)\n* ''Jelmezb\u00e1l: Egy csal\u00e1dreg\u00e9ny mozaikjai'' (2016; novel)\n* ''Harminc \u00e9v naps\u00fct\u00e9s'' (2017; short stories)\n* ''Vera'' (2019; novel)\n* ''Magamr\u00f3l t\u00f6bbet'' (2020; poetry)\n\n==Awards and honours==\n* [[S\u00e1ndor Br\u00f3dy Prize]] (2002)<ref name=\"magvetobio\" />\n* {{ill|Gy\u00f6rgy Faludy Prize|hu|Faludy Gy\u00f6rgy-d\u00edj}} (2004)<ref name=\"magvetobio\" />\n* {{ill|Tibor D\u00e9ry Prize|hu|D\u00e9ry Tibor-d\u00edj}} (2004)<ref name=\"magvetobio\" />\n* [[Attila J\u00f3zsef Prize]] (2006)<ref name=\"magvetobio\" />\n* {{ill|AEGON Art Prize|hu|AEGON m\u0171v\u00e9szeti d\u00edj}} (2012)<ref name=\"magvetobio\" /><ref name=\"aegonbio\" />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Grecso, Krisztian}}\n[[Category:Hungarian male novelists]]\n[[Category:Hungarian male poets]]\n[[Category:21st-century Hungarian novelists]]\n[[Category:21st-century Hungarian male writers]]\n[[Category:Attila J\u00f3zsef Prize recipients]]\n[[Category:1976 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "name_user": "Einstein2", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eBiography", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kriszti%C3%A1n_Grecs%C3%B3"}
{"title_page": "Tontine Trust", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Tontine Trust\n| logo = TontineTrust_logo.png\n| logo_size = \n| type = Fintech\n| genre = \n| foundation = 2017\n| founder = {{Unbulleted list|[[Dean McClelland]]}}\n| location_country = Hong Kong\n| location = <!-- this parameter modifies \"Headquarters\" -->\n| origins = \n| key_people = {{Unbulleted list|[[Dean McClelland]]|Richard Fullmer|Michael Neish|Richard Kent}}\n| area_served = \n| industry = [[Pensions]]\n| products = [[Tontine]] Pensions\n| operating_income = \n| net_income = \n| num_employees = \n| parent = \n| divisions = \n| subsid = \n| owner = \n| logo_caption = Live Long & Prosper\u00ae\n| website = {{URL|tontine.com}}\n| dissolved = \n| footnotes = \n}}\n'''TontineTrust''' is a [[Fintech]] developing a digital pensions platform which supports the creation & operation of fully-digital pension systems which adhere to or are derived from the [[Tontine]] principle.\n\nThe company is preparing to launch several international pension products for consumers including one of Europe's first [[Pan-European Pension]] Products the legislation for which is designed to encourage new types of lifetime income pensions for Europe's consumers and to develop a safer, more cost-efficient and transparent market in affordable\nand voluntary personal pension savings that can be managed on a pan-European scale<ref>https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/PDF/?uri=CELEX:32019R1238&from=EN</ref>.\n\n== Tontine Pensions ==\nTontines were invented in 1653 as an alternative to the unpopular Roman Empire era annua which in modern times is referred to as an [[annuity]]. They enable subscribers to share or pool their [[Longevity risk]], i.e. the risk of living a very long life and running out of money in retirement.\n\n== The Platform ==\nThe Tontine Trust platform is designed to accommodate pure Tontine Pensions as well as modern derivatives of which including:\n*Defined Ambition pensions\n*Target Benefit pensions\n*Collective Defined Contribution pensions or [[CDC Pensions]]\n\n== Awards ==\nIn October 2019, McClelland accepted an award on behalf of Tontine Trust from the [[Transparency Task Force]], presented by its founder [[Andy Agathangelou]],<ref>https://issuu.com/andyagathangelou/docs/transparency_times__42_october_2019</ref> in recognition of his & Tontine Trust's efforts towards increasing transparency in financial services.\n\n== Notable Media Coverage ==\n\n*{{cite interview |title=Bringing Tontines back from the Dead with Dean McClelland |last=McClelland |first=Dean |subjectlink=Dean McClelland |interviewer=Max Wiethe |work=[[Real Vision (US based Global Financial News Network)|Real Vision]] |publisher=[[Real Vision]] |location=New York |date=February 17, 2020 |url=https://www.realvision.com/shows/the-interview/videos/bringing-tontines-back-from-the-dead}}\n*{{cite news\n|title=Fintech's Answer To The Global Retirement Crisis\n|last=Mitchell\n|first=Olivia S.\n|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/pensionresearchcouncil/2018/01/30/fintechs-answer-to-the-global-retirement-crisis/\n|newspaper=[[Forbes]]\n|date=January 30, 2018\n|language=\n|archive-url=\n|archive-date=\n|url-status=\n|quote=Fintech innovators have the multi-trillion-dollar global retirement income market in their sights. \n}}\n\n== References ==\n<!--<nowiki>\nSee http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Footnotes for an explanation of how to generate footnotes using the <ref> and </ref> tags, and the template below. \n</nowiki>-->\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://www.tontine.com/ Organisation Website]\n\n{{Uncategorized|date=April 2020}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Tontine Trust\n| logo = TontineTrust_logo.png\n| logo_size = \n| type = Fintech\n| genre = \n| foundation = 2017\n| founder = {{Unbulleted list|[[Dean McClelland]]}}\n| location_country = Hong Kong\n| location = <!-- this parameter modifies \"Headquarters\" -->\n| origins = \n| key_people = {{Unbulleted list|[[Dean McClelland]]|Richard Fullmer|Michael Neish|Richard Kent}}\n| area_served = \n| industry = [[Pensions]]\n| products = [[Tontine]] Pensions\n| operating_income = \n| net_income = \n| num_employees = \n| parent = \n| divisions = \n| subsid = \n| owner = \n| logo_caption = Live Long & Prosper\u00ae\n| website = {{URL|tontine.com}}\n| dissolved = \n| footnotes = \n}}\n'''TontineTrust''' is a [[Fintech]] developing a digital pensions platform which supports the creation & operation of fully-digital pension systems which adhere to or are derived from the [[Tontine]] principle.\n\nThe company is preparing to launch several international pension products for consumers including one of Europe's first [[Pan-European Pension]] Products the legislation for which is designed to encourage new types of lifetime income pensions for Europe's consumers and to develop a safer, more cost-efficient and transparent market in affordable\nand voluntary personal pension savings that can be managed on a pan-European scale.\n\n== Tontine Pensions ==\nTontines were invented in 1653 as an alternative to the unpopular Roman Empire era annua which in modern times is referred to as an [[annuity]]. They enable subscribers to share or pool their [[Longevity risk]], i.e. the risk of living a very long life and running out of money in retirement.\n\n== The Platform ==\nThe Tontine Trust platform is designed to accommodate pure Tontine Pensions as well as modern derivatives of which including:\n*Defined Ambition pensions\n*Target Benefit pensions\n*Collective Defined Contribution pensions or [[CDC Pensions]]\n\n== Awards ==\nIn October 2019, McClelland accepted an award on behalf of Tontine Trust from the [[Transparency Task Force]], presented by its founder [[Andy Agathangelou]],<ref>https://issuu.com/andyagathangelou/docs/transparency_times__42_october_2019</ref> in recognition of his & Tontine Trust's efforts towards increasing transparency in financial services.\n\n== Notable Media Coverage ==\n\n*{{cite interview |title=Bringing Tontines back from the Dead with Dean McClelland |last=McClelland |first=Dean |subjectlink=Dean McClelland |interviewer=Max Wiethe |work=[[Real Vision (US based Global Financial News Network)|Real Vision]] |publisher=[[Real Vision]] |location=New York |date=February 17, 2020 |url=https://www.realvision.com/shows/the-interview/videos/bringing-tontines-back-from-the-dead}}\n*{{cite news\n|title=Fintech's Answer To The Global Retirement Crisis\n|last=Mitchell\n|first=Olivia S.\n|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/pensionresearchcouncil/2018/01/30/fintechs-answer-to-the-global-retirement-crisis/\n|newspaper=[[Forbes]]\n|date=January 30, 2018\n|language=\n|archive-url=\n|archive-date=\n|url-status=\n|quote=Fintech innovators have the multi-trillion-dollar global retirement income market in their sights. \n}}\n\n== References ==\n<!--<nowiki>\nSee http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Footnotes for an explanation of how to generate footnotes using the <ref> and </ref> tags, and the template below. \n</nowiki>-->\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://www.tontine.com/ Organisation Website]\n\n{{Uncategorized|date=April 2020}}\n", "name_user": "Drinkllanito", "label": "safe", "comment": "added ref for the PEPP language", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tontine_Trust"}
